EXP NO: 5	

Sorting (Ascending and Descending order) of Data.

LEARNING OUTCOMES:

•	After completing this experiment, the students will be able to write and execute assembly language program to sort the n numbers in ascending/descending order using 8051 trainer kit.
EQUIPMENTS REQUIRED: 8051 trainer kit.          

THEORY:

Sorting is the process of arranging data elements in a particular order to make them easier to analyze, process, and retrieve. There are two main types of sorting: ascending and descending. In ascending order 
sorting, the data is arranged from the smallest value to the largest value, such as 12, 23, 45, and 89. In descending order sorting, the data is arranged from the largest value to the smallest value, such as 89, 
45, 23, and 12. Sorting plays an important role in computer programming and data management because it improves data organization, makes searching faster (for example, in binary search), and enhances the efficiency 
of various algorithms. 
